# kubectl apply

Declarative Management of Kubernetes (Docs)
https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/manage-kubernetes-objects/declarative-config/

O vídeo foi apenas explicação dos comandos, não executou nenhum.


# Comandos

kubectl apply -f filename.yml  // create/update resources in a file

kubectl apply -f myfile.yaml

kubectl apply -f myyaml/  // create/update a whole directory of yaml

kubectl apply -f https://bret.run/pod.yml  // create/update from a URL

curl -L https://bret.run/pod

start https://bret.run/pod.yml